What is 1e9?
1e9 is a scientific notation representation of the number 1,000,000,000 (one billion). It is a shorthand way to express large or very small numbers in a compact form. Specifically:

1e9 means 
1
×
1
0
9
1×10 
9
 , which is equivalent to 1,000,000,000.
Which language uses 1e9?
The notation 1e9 is commonly used in several programming languages, including:

C++ (which is the language in your code snippet)
Python
Java
JavaScript
Matlab
Ruby
In general, most modern programming languages support scientific notation (also called exponential notation) to express floating-point numbers.
